<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-211733/R-HSA-211733>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> , <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0043066> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "Stimulation of cell death by PAK-2 requires the generation and stabilization of the caspase-activated form, PAK-2p34 (Walter et al., 1998;Jakobi et al., 2003). Levels of proteolytically activated PAK-2p34 protein are controlled by ubiquitin-mediated proteolysis. PAK-2p34 but not full-length PAK-2 is degraded by the 26 S proteasome (Jakobi et al., 2003). It is not known whether ubiquitination and degradation of PAK-2p34 occurs in the cytoplasm or in the nucleus." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Regulation of activated PAK-2p34 by proteasome mediated degradation" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "Reviewed: Chang, E, 2008-05-21 00:05:41" , "Edited: Matthews, L, 2008-02-03 20:50:13" , "Authored: Jakobi, R, 2008-02-05 11:04:14" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Matthews, L, 2008-06-12 00:23:53" ;
